deck: Zelos is a main character from the Tales of Symphonia game/manga series. He is the Chosen of the Tethe'alla and originally meant to just keep tabs on Lloyd and his companions, Zelos becomes a necessary ally and close friend.
description:
Origin

Zelos Wilder possibly has one of the most complicated, if not the most complicated, origin in Tales of Symphonia. Zelos was born to a woman named Mylene Wilder and the at the time Chosen of Tethe'alla at in a forced relationship by the Oracle of Cruxis. He would grow up in a mansion in the Tethe'alla captial, Meltokio. With his mother already loving someone while being forced into a marriage, and his father already being another relationship, Zelos grew up neglected and distant from his parents, and only on occasion would his mother show him any maternal attention. The only real and constant paternal figure in Zelos' life would be the family butler, Sebastian. But because of his status as son to the Chosen, Zelos grew up in an aristocratic and uncaring society, this would further dampen Zelos' value of himself. Zelos' father had a half-elf mistress, and she would give birth to Zelos' half sister, Seles Wilder. Zelos and his Seles were rather close as children and often played with each other. Zelos and Seles' father would die at some point during their childhood and Seles would end up developing ailments. Seles' mother devised a plan to give her and her daughter a better life. Since Zelos was the first born child, he inherited the title of Chosen from his father, but if he were to die, Seles would become the Chosen and would then be granted the status and riches that comes with it.

Zelos was in the snow city of Flanoir, and he would mention this as the first day he saw snow. While Zelos was making a snowman with his mother, the half elf mistress attempted to kill Zelos with a magical attack. Zelos' mother would be caught in the crossfire. His mother died in front of him and the last thing she ever said to him was she had wished he had never been born. Due to the mistress' crimes, his sister Seles would be locked away for life in the SE abbey. This shaped Zelos into not caring and feeling like he was worthless. He put on a mask of false confidence and bravado to compensate for his lack of self-worth. Zelos would be raised by Sebastian and he attended the research institute of Syback and he used his status as Chosen and looks to further himself and take shortcuts in school, although he himself is rather intelligent regardless. At some point years later, Zelos would be approached by one of Cruxis' generals and asked that in exchange having to fulfill his duties as Chosen, he would become a spy for Cruxis. Zelos would accept due to not really caring about his status and his emotional torment from all the years of neglect and self hatred.

Major Story Arcs

Zelos is first encountered when Lloyd's group first makes it to Tethe'alla from their world of Sylvarant. He is seen with a group of girls and he tries to flirt with Lloyd's companions that are girls, so Raine and Colette who is in a doll like state. He helps the group negotiate with the King and Pope about saving Colette by using his status as Chosen, ranking only under the King himself. The King allows it and Zelos joins them, but only under the stipulation that they do not leave the world of Tethe'alla. Zelos is branded a traitor when the Pope learns of them trying to go to Iselia. Zelos leads the group into a trap to get the rheiards, but he makes it look like an accident. However, Pronyma, the general that had approached Zelos years ago to become their spy, is there leading the attack, but also the leader of the Renegades, Yuan, is there to take rheairds.

Zelos helps the team traverse through the sewers of Meltokio to get into the city, but they are encountered by Regal Bryant, an escaped convict. Zelos is almost killed but is saved by Presea. After getting to the Tethe'alla base, Zelos disappears and eventually comes back. When the group enters the Tower of Salvation, Zelos betrays the group and hands over Colette to Cruxis. The group is outraged but also hurt by Zelos' betrayal. When Lloyd is the only once left, he managed to get to the room where Colette is held, all of Lloyd's friends who he had thought died and sacrificed themselves to save him come appear in the room, it was revealed that it was actually Zelos who had saved them. Zelos then reveals his triple agent status, being a spy for Cruxis, to helping the Renegades, to being Lloyd's friend and companion to his group.Zelos and the team then manage to defeat the Pope and clear their names of being traitors as the Pope was an enemy of Cruxis. Zelos is the biggest supporter and protector of the female ninja, Sheena. He saves her from the Otherworldly Gate when it was about to close. Zelos and the group travel between the two worlds to defeat and make pacts with the Summon Spirits to try and help restore the flow of mana to both worlds.

Zelos and the group also destroy the main Desian base. Zelos uses his Chosen connections once again to convince the princess of Meltokio to get him and the group access into the restricted half-elf city of Heimdall. Zelos travels with the group there where Lloyd defeats Kratos in a duel. Kratos reveals the seal of the summon spirit Origin and the Cruxis Crystal of Mithos possesses Colette and escapes to Derris Kharlan. Zelos and the group manage to save Colette and the planetary body of the angelic city of Derris-Kharlan hovers the earth. Battling their way through, they finally reach Mithos, the starter of all this grief to create a world of lifeless beings to end all discrimination and resurrect his sister. The group defeats the twisted half-elf and destroy his Cruxis Crystal, ending his existance once and for all. After this, the group heads outside and Zelos watches on as Lloyd uses the Eternal Sword to fuse the worlds of Tethe'alla and Sylvarant back together and form the new Great Kharlan Tree. When the group goes their separate ways, Zelos uses his status as the Chosen to send an emissary of peace, and he chooses Sheena.

Tales of Symphonia: Dawn of the New World

Two years after the first series, Zelos makes his debut here by saving Emil and Marta from Richter in the rebuilt city of Palmacosta. Zelos later appears to help them again from Alice and Zelos tells her he will forget what she has done if she lives. He also is seen not liking Emil and Marta when they refer to Lloyd, who was framed for the destruction of Palmacosta years before the setting of new story, as a bastard. Zelos rejoins the group when his sister Seles is kidnapped. He is also the one to discover which of the two Lloyd's is the real one. He helps Emil and Marta finish their journey and defeat Richter from opening the gate to the monster world.

Powers and Abilities

Zelos possesses one of the Chosen's Cruxis Crystals. This an advanced crystal from a typical exsphere. This crystal grants Zelos superhuman abilities and various other powers. Due to the crystal, Zelos has superhuman strength, speed, agility, reflexes, and durability. Zelos is capable of cutting through small boulders with ease and can send people flying several meters away with his strikes. He has blocked attacks from opponents who could cause massive craters in the ground, showing his stopping power and durability. He can strike hard enough to harm opponents that could survive falls that would kill someone. He can perform complicated acrobatics with ease. He can move so fast that in short bursts of speed that he looks like he can teleport, even by doing so by leaping in the air so fast a group of enemies attacking him from all directions couldn't register his movement until he was descending from the air. He is durable enough to withstand falls that would kill someone and take blows from opponents that could cause massive craters in the ground. Due to his Cruxis Crystal, he can transfer his own energy into his sword or dagger to shoot out energy blasts that can rip the ground to shreds, or channel the energy in the blade to enhance its cutting power. Also due to his Cruxis Crystal, he can grow golden angelic wings that enable him to fly and access light elemental energy for attacks.

Zelos is a human, but he would receive elven blood transfusions as an infant to ready him for the Cruxis Crystal. Because of this, Zelos can perform moderate level magic capabilities of fire, electric, wind, and earth elements. He can also perform moderately strong healing spells. And due to the angelic energy he can access from his Cruxis Crystal, Zelos can use the divine energy for his own personal and strongest attack known as Shining Bind.

Aside from his abilities granted from the crystal, Zelos is an expert combatant. He has casually defeated groups of enemies without the need for a weapon. Zelos' preferred weapon is a dagger or sword, making use of them in his fluid and almost dance-like fighting style. Zelos is incredibly intelligent and cunning. He managed to play the three groups of the Renegades, Lloyd's party, and Cruxis without them figuring it out until he revealed it. Zelos also has an uncanny observation ability. This seems to extend from his womanizing, but he transitioned it into a general ability. He has noticed Lloyd getting only a slight belly from sneaking sweets. When Richter tried killed Marta and attacking Emil, Zelos saved them and told Richter to try his luck with that battered body, something Emil nor Marta could pick up on. Zelos was also the only character to pick up on the difference between the real and fake Lloyd, which he did by noticing the imposter's scent from his cologne.

Due to his status as Chosen, Zelos is also held in high rank amongst society, having power and authority exceeded only by the King.

Other Versions

Zelos appears in the OVA that was released in Japan since the game was so popular.
name: Zelos Wilder

deck: Young kid with the brain of a 60-year old Polish military general.
description:
History

All-New Marvel Now

Arrogant and Aggressive, Mikhail Zamoska is a expert militar armed with multiple machine-guns, granate and body armor, with the body of a children.

While his full story it's still unknown, it's known that he was a high rank in Polish military, a respected and feared General and when he died, the Polish military scientist try and experiment for transfer his the full conscience in to a baby clone of itself.

"Created" for battle, Mikhail Zamoska, now calling itself The Baby Killer, join the new Euroforce led by the Black Knight.

While in Italy, under the city of Velletri, he and his team came into contact with some members of the Avengers and fter some clarification, both groups were surrounded by Morgan le Fay and her army of the dead, and fight her.

Powers

Given his life as General of the Polish Army, Mikhail have a great experience in tactics, strategy, military training for hand to hand combat and with various type of weapon. In mission, he usually carrie a large arsenal of weapon, shooting with a pair of machinegun and launching granade all at the same time and he also wear full-combat battle armor.

While his mental skill are cleary that of an expert militar with high rank, including diplomacy, leadership and others, his physical ability must yet been specified. He have showed both agility and strength far above that of average childs of his age, so may be supposed that his body is not a "normal" clone, but one enanched to some kind of super-soldier level.

Notes

Is not know if the process of "cloning - mind transfer" can be repeat by Polish government. In this case, he may die/resurrect multiple time, just as the LMD do, or Mikhail may even exist in different body. Anyway, at present state, this are only hypothesis.

Also, he usually refere to itself as THE Baby Killer, and in the same way his name is presented in panel, so perhaps his battle name is "The Baby Killer" and not simply "Baby Killer".
name: Baby Killer

deck: Being composed of artificially engineered alien compounds.
description:
History

All-New Marvel Now

Before becoming a member of the new Euroforce, Franco Fibbri was a famous soccer player, stated as "the most paid soccer player in the world".

When he retire, he spent all his money on a dangerous project to imbue himself with strange and unidentified alien substance which transformed him into the golden compound being. He take the battle name of Sliver.

When a tv show ask him why he have chose to undergo this transformation, he state that he was bored of anyone asking for his money for aiding children: now he have no more money, he used them to become a superhero (he may or maybe not joking).

He was then made a member of the new team Euroforce led by the Black Knight, and durring a mission he, along with the rest of the team, fight with some Avengers against Morgan Le Fay and her army of the dead, under the Italian City of Velletri.

Powers

Sliver is now made of alien compound that give them a still unclear range of powers. He was able to growth large spike all over his body, suggesting that he may "shapeshift" as some sort of "liquid metal", and also have used his compound to cauterize and partially heal some Hawkeye wounds.

Note

While not still specified, given the mutation caused in the body of Franco Fibbri, may be supposed that the alien substance used on him have some connection with the Klyntar race.
name: Sliver

deck: Mysterious Member of the new Euroforce.
description:
History

All-New Marvel Now

Little or none is know about the origin of the member of the new Euroforce called Tumult.

She is Spanish and have received her power-glove as a gift from some mysterious benefactor [that she seem to know], but other things about her must yet be discovered.

While she have incredible devastanting power, she appear to be the least trained member of the team. Anyway, she have shown some friendly rivality with her teammate Swordswoman.

While in Italy, under the city of Velletri, she and her team came into contact with some members of the Avengers. After some clarification, both groups were surrounded by Morgan le Fay and her army of the dead, and fight her.

Powers

Tumult possess a pair of power-glove wich permit her to discharge incredible ammount of energy, that she usually release on the ground causing large seismic wave. It's not know if that energy can be used for a direct hit instead of a seismic strike.

Also, is not clear if the whole seismic power came from the gloves or if the gloves only amplify, or permit her to use, some sort of mutant/inhuman power that she may posses.

Note

The use of power-gloves by Tumult highly remeber one of the original members of the Euroforce, Blue Condor, which used power-gloves to manage her gravity-control powers. Even if that may be a coincidence, it's also possible that is a clear reference, an homage to the original characters [being Blue Condor the first member of the team to die in battle], or also may be a reference to some unknown tie between Tumult and Blue Condor.
name: Tumult

deck: Swordsman's daughter.
description:
History

All-New Marvel Now

Marjorie Adelynn is the daughter of former Avenger's member Swordsman [Jacques Duquesne].

She grew up without her father in her life, but managed to follow in his footsteps, in spite of his mother will.

Going by the name Swordswoman, she joined the newly formed team Euroforce, led by the Black Knight.

While in Italy, under the city of Velletri, she and her team came into contact with some members of the Avengers and Swodswoman fought Spider-Woman not knowing who she was. After some clarification, both groups were surrounded by Morgan le Fay and her army of the dead, and fight her.

Powers

Even if where she have been trained have not been stated, Adelynn appear to be an expert in hand to hand combat and acrobatics attack and became highly skilled in the use of a sword. Even if she is a normal human, her agility seem to match that of Jessica Drew, which ability are genetically enanched.

She use a special sword made of energy, that can be turned-off and hidden in her belt.
name: Swordswoman
